{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Grass|type2=Poison}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/GO|species=Oddish}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Grass|prevnum=042|prev=Golbat|nextnum=044|next=Gloom|roundleft=bl|roundright=br}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Oddish\n|jname=ナゾノクサ\n|tmname=Nazonokusa\n|ndex=043\n|jdex=083\n|hdex=088\n|hdex6=091\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=105\n|fbrow=126\n|abrow=114\n|obrow=127\n|opbrow=012\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Grass\n|type2=Poison\n|category=Weed\n|height-ftin=1\'08"\n|height-m=0.5\n|weight-lbs=11.9\n|weight-kg=5.4\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Chlorophyll\n|abilityd=Run Away\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Grass\n|eggcycles=20\n|evtotal=1\n|evsa=1\n|expyield=64\n|oldexp=78\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|gendercode=127\n|color=Blue\n|catchrate=255\n|body=07\n|pokefordex=oddish\n|generation=1\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Oddish\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ナゾノクサ\'\'\' \'\'Nazonokusa\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Grass|Poison}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation I]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] into {{p|Gloom}} starting at [[level]] 21, which evolves into {{p|Vileplume}} when exposed to a [[Leaf Stone]] or into {{p|Bellossom}} when exposed to a [[Sun Stone]].\n\n==Biology==\nOddish is a Pokémon that resembles a blue plant bulb. It has a round body, beady red eyes, a small mouth, and ovoid feet. Five large, green leaves sprout from its head. As demonstrated in [[EP137|the anime]], these leaves are prehensile and can be used to scale vertical surfaces and catch light objects. Known by the scientific name \'\'Oddium Wanderus\'\', Oddish lives in {{DL|List of Pokémon by habitat|Grassland Pokémon|grasslands}}. A nocturnal Pokémon, Oddish buries its sensitive body in the ground during the day to avoid the sun and fool predators. If its leaves are pulled in this state, it will respond by shrieking horribly. It starts to move when its leaves begin absorbing moonlight, which it uses to grow. Oddish will wander up to 1000 feet (300 meters) during the night to scatter its seeds and find a nutrient-rich patch of soil in which to plant itself. The more fertile the earth, the glossier its leaves will be. It is thought that its feet become like tree roots while planted. In the past, {{m|Petal Dance}} was its [[signature move]].\n\n==In the anime==\n[[File:Oddish M21.png|thumb|left|250px|Oddish in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n===In the main series===\n====Major appearances====\nOddish debuted in \'\'[[EP010|Bulbasaur and the Hidden Village]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon under [[Melanie]]\'s care in the [[Hidden Village]]. {{an|Misty}} attempted to catch it with {{TP|Misty|Starmie}} because she thought it was cute, but {{AP|Bulbasaur}} attacked her, and Misty later apologized. It reappeared in a flashback in \'\'[[EP225|Bulbasaur... the Ambassador!]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP137|Foul Weather Friends]]\'\', under the ownership of {{OBP|Mariah|EP137}}. It wanted to fly with its {{p|Hoppip}} friends, even trying to color itself pink like a Hoppip. Though it never flies, it still proved itself to be powerful enough to defeat {{TRT}} on its own.\n\nThree Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP239|Whichever Way the Wind Blows]]\'\', under the ownership of {{OBP|Steven|EP239}}. He uses them to study the [[evolution]] of {{t|Grass}} Pokémon in the area. Multiple other Oddish also appeared in the same episode.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP014|Electric Shock Showdown]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP015|Battle Aboard the St. Anne]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP026|Pokémon Scent-sation!]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon in [[Celadon Gym]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP027|Hypno\'s Naptime]]\'\', where it was seen in [[HopHopHop Town]]\'s [[Pokémon Center]].\n\nTwo Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP028|Pokémon Fashion Flash]]\'\' as some of the Pokémon seen on [[Scissor Street]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP030|Sparks Fly for Magnemite]]\'\', where it was seen in [[Gringey City]]\'s [[Pokémon Center]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in a fantasy in \'\'[[EP031|Dig Those Diglett!]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP034|The Kangaskhan Kid]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP043|The March of the Exeggutor Squad]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP047|A Chansey Operation]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[EP048|Holy Matrimony!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Jessebelle]]. It is now a Vileplume.\n\nA Trainer\'s Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP056|The Ultimate Test]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP057|The Breeding Center Secret]]\'\'.\n\nA Trainer\'s Oddish appeared in \'\'[[M01|Mewtwo Strikes Back]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon {{OBP|Mewtwo|original series}} defeated while serving for {{an|Giovanni}}.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[PK01|Pikachu\'s Vacation]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Theme Park]].\n\nMultiple Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP065|Showdown at the Po-ké Corral]]\'\', where they were among the Pokémon living at [[Professor Oak\'s Laboratory]]. They reappeared in \'\'[[HS04|Showdown at the Oak Corral]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Trainers\' Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP080|Friends to the End]]\'\' during the closing ceremonies of the [[Indigo League]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP081|Pallet Party Panic]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon at a party in [[Pallet Town]].\n\nMultiple {{DL|List of alternately colored Pokémon in the anime|Pink Pokémon|pink}} Oddish appeared in {{TRT}}\'s fantasy in \'\'[[EP088|In the Pink]]\'\'.\n\nTwo Oddish appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[EP100|Wherefore Art Thou, Pokémon?]]\'\', one each under the ownership of {{OBP|Ralph|EP100}} and {{OBP|Emily|EP100}}.\n\nMultiple Oddish appeared in \'\'[[M02|The Power of One]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn2|wild}} Oddish appeared in \'\'[[PK04|Pikachu\'s Rescue Adventure]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP122|Flower Power]]\'\' as a part of [[Florando]]\'s annual [[Pokémon Exhibition]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in a flashback in \'\'[[EP129|Ignorance is Blissey]]\'\', under the ownership of the [[Pokémon Nurse School]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP146|Tricks of the Trade]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon seen at the [[Pokémon Swap Meet]] in [[Palmpona]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[PK07|Pikachu & Pichu]]\'\' as a resident of [[Big Town]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP157|The Fortune Hunters]]\'\' as one of the Pokémon stolen by [[Butch]] and [[Cassidy]].\n\nThree Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP169|Beauty and the Breeder]]\'\', with one under the ownership of a Trainer and the other two under the ownership of different {{tc|Pokémon Breeder}}s participating in [[Pokémon Beauty Contest|a Pokémon breeding competition]].\n\nThree Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP178|The Grass Route]]\'\', with two being {{pkmn2|wild}} and one being under the ownership of a Trainer competing in the [[Grass Tournament]].\n\nA {{pkmn2|talking}} Oddish appeared in [[Simon]]\'s purported flashback in \'\'[[EP195|The Poké Spokesman]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Oddish appeared in \'\'[[M04|Celebi: The Voice of the Forest]]\'\' and \'\'[[M05|Pokémon Heroes: Latios & Latias]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[PK10|Pikachu\'s PikaBoo]]\'\'.\n\nMultiple Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP225|Bulbasaur... the Ambassador!]]\'\', where they were among the feuding Pokémon at Professor Oak\'s Laboratory.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[The Legend of Thunder!]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP235|Talkin\' \'Bout an Evolution]]\'\', where it fell sick due to [[Team Rocket]]\'s experiments.\n\nMultiple Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP252|Fangs for Nothin\']]\'\' as inhabitants of the [[Dragon Holy Land]].\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP272|Johto Photo Finish]]\'\', where it was one of the Pokémon being fed by {{Tracey}} at Professor Oak\'s Laboratory.\n\nThree Oddish appeared in \'\'[[EP274|Hoenn Alone!]]\'\', where they were among the Pokémon that were having trouble with the {{p|Haunter}} from the area they lived in. {{A