owns an Oddish in [[The Electric Tale of Pikachu]]. It is one of the few Pokémon that Ash owns in the {{pkmn|manga}} but not in the {{pkmn|anime}}. It first appeared in \'\'[[ET08|You Gotta Have Friends]]\'\'. Its capture was not shown, and it instead appeared with several of Ash\'s other Pokémon with a note explaining that "Ash has been very busy since the last comic".\n\n===In the movie adaptations===\nAn Oddish appeared in the {{ma|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction|manga adaptation}} of \'\'[[M17|Diancie and the Cocoon of Destruction]]\'\' as a resident of [[Allearth Forest]].\n\n===In the Pokémon Adventures manga===\nOddish debuted as a silhouette when {{adv|Green}} talks about {{adv|Mew}} in \'\'[[PS017|The Jynx Jinx]]\'\'.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS063|Extricated from Exeggutor]]\'\', multiple Oddish were seen during the mass migration of Pokémon at the [[Seafoam Islands]]. They appeared again in a flashback in \'\'[[PS142|Really Remoraid]]\'\', where a {{p|Remoraid}} migration was being described as remarkably similar to their own.\n\n{{adv|Gold}} owns an Oddish, which he kept at his house in \'\'[[PS091|Murkrow Row]]\'\'.\n\n{{adv|Crystal}} {{pkmn2|caught}} an Oddish on her way to [[Professor Elm]]\'s Laboratory in \'\'[[PS118|Three Cheers for Chikorita]]\'\'.\n\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Oddish appeared in \'\'[[PS204|Plugging Past Electrike I]]\'\'.\n\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[PS418|Deprogramming Porygon-Z]]\'\', under the ownership of an {{tc|Aroma Lady}}.\n\nIn \'\'[[PS442|Out-Odding Oddish]]\'\', [[Jet]], a notable competitor in the [[Pokéathlon]]\'s Speed Course, used an Oddish to compete with {{adv|Gold}}. Another Trainer also used one the same chapter.\n\n===In the Pokémon Battle Frontier manga===\nAn Oddish appeared in \'\'[[CBF4|Introducing the Frontier Brains!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Gold & Silver: The Golden Boys manga===\nA Trainer\'s Oddish appeared in \'\'[[GB23|Let\'s Fight For The Future!!]]\'\'.\n\n===In the Pokémon Gotta Catch \'Em All manga===